  "doc_id": "30383",
  "text": "This hypomethylation of D4Z4 correlates with loss of several chromatin marks including H3K9me3, the heterochromatin-binding protein HP1γ and cohesion [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . However, hypomethylation of D4Z4 is not sufficient to trigger this loss as ICF patients, which are deficient in DNMT3b and show no FSHD symptoms (47), still retain the H3K9me3 marker at D4Z4 despite extensive hypomethylation [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The presence of repressive H3K9me3 at D4Z4 is dependent on the SUV39H1 methylase, with HP1γ and cohesion recruitment a downstream process [CITATION_5] . Supporting a functional link to D4Z4 repression, inhibition of SUV39H1 leads to a reduction in H3K9me3 and increased transcription of DUX4 [CITATION_6] .",
